<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd" MadCap:lastBlockDepth="6" MadCap:lastHeight="791" MadCap:lastWidth="1537">
    <body>
        <p>NetHelp installed locally can be given the Mark of the Web (MOTW). This means that anyone viewing your NetHelp locally will not receive a browser security warning first. (This ActiveX security warning is dependent on the security settings of the machine.) MOTW adds commentary text to every HTML file in the NetHelp target. It is turned on using the <span class="Emphasis">Mark of the Web</span> check box in the Help Targets dialog. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet1">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../D2H/Output/Editing-Target-Settings.htm">Editing Target Settings</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet2">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../D2H/Legacy-HTML5/Output/Editing-Target-Settings.htm">Editing Target Settings</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
        <MadCap:dropDown>
            <MadCap:dropDownHead>
                <MadCap:dropDownHotspot>MOTW Issues</MadCap:dropDownHotspot>
            </MadCap:dropDownHead>
            <MadCap:dropDownBody>
                <p>There are some issues with the MOTW. For example, links to PDF will not open from NetHelp files using the MOTW. To learn more see:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><a href="http://jtfassociates.com/using-the-mark-of-the-web-motw/" target="_blank">http://jtfassociates.com/using-the-mark-of-the-web-motw/</a>
                    </li>
                    <li><a href="http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms537628(VS.85).aspx" target="_blank">http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms537628(VS.85).aspx</a>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </MadCap:dropDownBody>
        </MadCap:dropDown>
        <MadCap:dropDown>
            <MadCap:dropDownHead>
                <MadCap:dropDownHotspot>How to Install NetHelp on a Client Machine </MadCap:dropDownHotspot>
            </MadCap:dropDownHead>
            <MadCap:dropDownBody>
                <ol>
                    <li>Build the NetHelp target. </li>
                    <li>Copy the contents of the NetHelp folder to the desired directory. </li>
                    <li>To view the output, open the <span class="Emphasis">index.htm</span> file. &#160;</li>
                </ol>
                <p>You can rename the NetHelp destination folder using the <span class="Emphasis">Folder field</span> of the Help Targets dialog (<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet1">from the <span class="Emphasis">Target</span> ribbon, click <span class="Emphasis">Target Properties</span></MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet2">from the <span class="Emphasis">Home</span> ribbon, click <img src="../../../../Images/Shared/Co-D2-Fl/Interface/Buttons/Arrow-btn.png" class="ReduceButtonSize" /></MadCap:conditionalText>). The default file name can be renamed using the <span class="Emphasis">Default file</span> field.</p>
            </MadCap:dropDownBody>
        </MadCap:dropDown>
        <MadCap:dropDown>
            <MadCap:dropDownHead class="OnlineOnly">
                <MadCap:dropDownHotspot>Note</MadCap:dropDownHotspot>
            </MadCap:dropDownHead>
            <MadCap:dropDownBody>
                <p class="note">NetHelp installed locally will not open in Chrome, IE Edge, or Opera because of limitations with those browsers, but it will display in all other browsers. NetHelp deployed on a web server will open in Chrome, IE Edge, and Opera.</p>
            </MadCap:dropDownBody>
        </MadCap:dropDown>
    </body>
</html>